This paper deals with decision-theoretic control of search, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves game-playing, which falls under the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper uses analytic techniques, which can be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper discusses algorithms, which can be classified under programming languages (cs.PL).
